nib.text:
A standoff has ended in St. Paul after police tactically disengaged.

Police responded to a residence on the 700 block of Jackson Street around 2:45 p.m. Monday after a man was reportedly armed with multiple knives. Another man was also inside the home.

Once officers arrived on the scene, the man reportedly refused to cooperate.

SWAT team members and hostage negotiators were called to the location to make contact with the man.

At one point during the standoff, a man left the building with a minor injury. EMS tended to the person, although it was unclear how he became injured. 

After several hours, police determined the allegedly armed man was no longer a danger to themselves or others and officers decided to tactically disengage.

Police said they are still investigating the incident.
